CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1946, pg. 2 reads: "Color Doesn't Matter - James Cellini, Aliquippa resident undergoes infra-red ray treatment at the hands of Dr. Max E. Johnson of Aliquippa.  Mr. Cellini says: "Dr. Johnson is a good doctor; he treats all my family when we're sick."  Dr. Johnson was formerly resident physician at Denmar State Hospital in West Virginia.  He is now on the courtesy staff at Rochester General Hospital in Rochester, Pa. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: James Cellini, lying on examination table, and Dr. Max E. Johnson wearing stethoscope around neck, in medical office with faucets, scale, and large lamp
